Resolve backward compatibility issues

Resolve backward compatibility issues #1 - ActionBarSherlock on splashscreen
This resolves a startup issue on older devices. The Theme.Splash needs to have a Theme.Sherlock-related theme, this commit fixes that.

Resolve backward compatibility issues #2 - Background graphics
Older Android versions did not have a background setting for RelativeLayout, so better use an additional ImageView. For buttons, I had to create a convenience routine for setting the bg.

Resolve backward compatibility issues #2 - Background graphics
Older Android versions did not have a background setting for RelativeLayout, so better use an additional ImageView. For buttons, I had to create a convenience routine for setting the bg.

Resolve backward compatibility issues #3 - Overflow menu, ActionBarSherlock etc.
There's a known inconsistency in handling the ActionBar overflow items in Android. This version solves this by using a similar menu item instead of the "default" overflow. It's confirmed to be working on 2.1, 2.3 and 4.2.2.

Fixing drawing cache issue on ArticleSet
This is a temporary fix only, which solves the issue when the contents of a given articleset won't appear because running out of drawing cache. This is caused by (?) using the WebView in ScrollView, which seems to be a bad practice. I call this temporary, because it won't solve problems long-term: displaying the logo and the footer within the HTML could do that.
